Orit Mizrachi

Location
New York, NY


Industry

Financial Services



Business Segment

Global Market Strategies




Orit Mizrachi has served as our Chief Operating Officer since 2014 and is a Managing Director of Carlyle. She is also the chief operating officer of NFIC.  Since joining Carlyle early in 2010, Ms. Mizrachi has been involved in various roles and most recently served as the Director of Operations for the GMS platform from 2011 to 2014.
Prior to joining Carlyle, Ms. Mizrachi worked in the hedge fund industry as the chief financial officer of Carlyle Blue Wave Management L.P. from 2007 to 2008 and as controller at Sagamore Hill Capital Management L.P. from 2000 to 2006, two multi-strategy hedge funds. Ms. Mizrachi started her career at Goldstein Golub & Kessler LLP as an auditor in their financial services group.
She has a Bachelor of Science in Accounting from the State University of New York at Albany.





































