Orit Mizrachi 












Ms Orit Mizrachi  

Overviewrit Mizrachi is a Vice President in the Fund Management group of Carlyle's Investor Services. She is based in New York.
Prior to joining the Fund Management group, Ms. Mizrachi was a consultant to several Carlyle initiatives. Prior to joining Carlyle, she spent eight years as Controller/CFO of Carlyle-Blue Wave Management LP and Controller of Sagamore Hill Capital Management LP, two multi-strategy hedge funds. Ms. Mizrachi started her career at Goldstein, Golub & Kessler LLP and left there as a Manager.Ms. Mizrachi received a B.S. in accounting with minors in business administration and Hebrew from SUNY Albany, and has been a CPA in the state of New York since 1997.


